Properties.PostHtml:
Neal unpacked 4 truths in understanding the Greatest Story ever told.

  • Our Purpose: Relationship with God - we have been set apart from the rest of creation to experience life with God
  • Our Problem: Sin - which separates us from that intended relationship with Him
  • God’s Remedy: Jesus - He solves the problem of sin and brings us back into right relationship with God and finally
  • God’s Promise: Grace - a promise that through Jesus we will never be separated from our relationship with God again

Properties.PostHtml: Marti walked through 4 movements in responding to the good news of Jesus and making a decision to make him the Lord and leader of your life- Belief, Confession, Repentance and Baptism. Again, Belief, Confession and Repentance are central to that decision, while Baptism is a response to that decision.

Properties.PostHtml: Michael reminded us of some important aspects about baptism- that through baptism we are identifying ourselves with Jesus, we are being obedient to what he asked of us, that baptism only comes after a decision to follow Him and that the step of baptism symbolizes Jesus’ death, burial and resurrection.
